Committee members and the Group Support Team will be available after the meeting to answer questions and discuss any matters of concern. Robert Brewer is an ex Soldier and a retired Police Ofcer. He fell into the industry 6 years ago as a TV/Film Extra after a visit to his local library. He has been in over 40 different features, from Hollywood Blockbusters (Batman, Bond, Wonder Woman) and low-budget lms (Blinded by the Light) to TV dramas, soaps and comedies, and even a couple of adverts. He will tell us about some of the productions that he's been on, explain how he became involved in the industry and how anyone can do it. The Roles of a Supporting Artist Robert Brewer
December Members Meeting 2 THURSDAY 4TH DECEMBER BOOKING REQUIRED Please note that our members open meeting in December will be the rst Thursday of the month, on 4 th December at 2pm. At this meeting we will be making our own entertainment and, as it will be getting near to Christmas, there will be a seasonal theme. Back by popular demand after their performance at our AGM, our own Uke-Troupe will entertain us with a variety of songs, there will be opportunity for audience participation and a few of our members have agreed to brave the stage for a mini panto. Our refreshments will include mince pies and bucks zz. As seating in the Corn Exchange is limited, entry will be strictly current members only. Admission will still be free but, to avoid having to turn members away at the door, seats will need to be pre-booked. Our booking-in system for that day will be able to conrm whether you have pre-booked. Booking will open after the open meeting on 13 th November Members attending that meeting will be able to book in person then, and anyone not able to attend the meeting is welcome to come along at 3.15pm to book a ticket. Please note no bookings will be taken before the meeting. Members with internet access will be able to book via the blue envelope on the web site, in the same way as for outings, but this option will not be active until 3pm on 13 th November. The link for this event is here: https://u3aivo.uk/dec4/

Woodbridge was very interesting particularly on the quay where, in the Long Shed, a reconstruction of the Anglo Saxon burial ship found at Sutton Hoo is being built. Moving on to Framlingham Castle in the afternoon we had time to explore the Castle and for the more energetic walk around the walls. Sue Belcher/Val Bonny

Group News 7 New Member Event We will be holding an event for all new members in the last 9 months on Friday 7th November. The objective of the meeting is to welcome new members and advise on how you can get the most from the u3a - whether it be joining the numerous groups, attending outings, theatre trips or the monthly open meeting. Ian Pask Environment Matters This group has not met for the last few months, but a number of members have expressed enthusiasm for it being re-established in the New Year. A meeting has been arranged for Thursday 6 th November, 2-3pm in the small meeting room downstairs at the Methodist Church, to discuss how it can be organised and a possible programme. All the current members have been contacted directly, but if any other members would like to express an interest in the subject and nd out more about the group, they will be welcome to join the meeting. If you plan to attend, it would be helpful, but not essential, if you could let us know via the blue envelope on the group page here: https://stivescambs.u3asite.uk/ u3a_groups/environment-matters/ Italian Improvers We are a small friendly group who have a knowledge of Italian pronunciation and reading. Some weeks we read aloud and translate. We also follow a book by Olly Richards, Easy Italian news and use Italian Grammar BBC. The intention of the group is to enjoy Italian language and the culture. We have 4 regular attendees but have space for 2-3 more. We meet every Monday at Rockabillies upstairs. I am the coordinator but each member contributes in the u3a way. We would welcome some new regular members please come along and see us. Heather Wells https://stivescambs.u3asite.uk/ u3a_groups/italian-improvers/ Canasta Canasta is an enjoyable social pastime and helps keep the mind active. We are a lively group and beginners are welcome as well as experienced players. We would welcome more members. Vivien Brown https://stivescambs.u3asite.uk/ u3a_groups/canasta/
Data Protection and Privacy Policy Review 8 We have undertaken a general review of our Data Protection and Privacy Policy documents and practices, via a small sub-committee of Trustees and u3a member volunteers with knowledge and experience in this area. In so doing, we have drawn upon guidance from the national u3a and good practice from other u3as both locally and regionally. As a result, updated versions of the Data Protection Policy, Legitimate Interest Assessment and Privacy Notice have been approved by the Committee and published on the website. All of these can be found under the Documents header on the u3a Homepage by clicking on the Policies and Procedures drop-down box, or via this link - https://u3aivo.uk/policies-and-procedures/. Peter Cooper, Chair Many members of St Ives u3a will remember our founder member and first chairman, Peter Baker, and may be interested to know that there will be a presentation by Peters daughter, Helen Cooper, based on her grandfather Tom Bakers war diary. To be held at the St Ives Civic Society meeting on Friday 21st November at The Free Church, 7.30pm. The talk will detail his incarceration at Stalag Luft III, the subsequent long march home, and the family history that inspired the establishment of the St Ives Books of Honour and Remembrance. Entrance is free to Civic Society members, non-members are always welcome and a donation of 3 is requested to help cover costs. The Story of Wing Commander Baker DFC DFM
